{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Ladies and gentlemen, gather around."},{"time":2000,"text":"I would love to share with you a story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":5000,"text":"Once upon a time"},{"time":7000,"text":"in 19th century Germany,"},{"time":9000,"text":"there was the book."},{"time":11000,"text":"Now during this time,"},{"time":13000,"text":"the book was the king of storytelling."},{"time":15000,"text":"It was venerable."},{"time":17000,"text":"It was ubiquitous."},{"time":19000,"text":"But it was a little bit boring."},{"time":23000,"text":"Because in its 400 years of existence,"},{"time":26000,"text":"storytellers never evolved the book"},{"time":28000,"text":"as a storytelling device."},{"time":30000,"text":"But then one author arrived,"},{"time":32000,"text":"and he changed the game forever."},{"time":36000,"text":"(Music)"},{"time":38000,"text":"His name was Lothar,"},{"time":40000,"text":"Lothar Meggendorfer."},{"time":43000,"text":"Lothar Meggendorfer put his foot down,"},{"time":46000,"text":"and he said, \"Genug ist genug!\""},{"time":52000,"text":"He grabbed his pen,"},{"time":54000,"text":"he snatched his scissors."},{"time":56000,"text":"This man refused to fold to the conventions of normalcy"},{"time":58000,"text":"and just decided to fold."},{"time":60000,"text":"History would know Lothar Meggendorfer"},{"time":62000,"text":"as -- who else? --"},{"time":64000,"text":"the world's first true inventor"},{"time":66000,"text":"of the children's pop-up book."},{"time":69000,"text":"(Music)"},{"time":71000,"text":"For this delight and for this wonder,"},{"time":73000,"text":"people rejoiced."},{"time":75000,"text":"(Cheering)"},{"time":78000,"text":"They were happy because the story survived,"},{"time":81000,"text":"and that the world would keep on spinning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":83000,"text":"Lothar Meggendorfer wasn't the first"},{"time":85000,"text":"to evolve the way a story was told,"},{"time":87000,"text":"and he certainly wasn't the last."},{"time":89000,"text":"Whether storytellers realized it or not,"},{"time":91000,"text":"they were channeling Meggendorfer's spirit"},{"time":93000,"text":"when they moved opera to vaudville,"},{"time":98000,"text":"radio news to radio theater,"},{"time":101000,"text":"film to film in motion"},{"time":104000,"text":"to film in sound, color, 3D,"},{"time":107000,"text":"on VHS and on DVD."},{"time":109000,"text":"There seemed to be no cure for this Meggendorferitis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":112000,"text":"And things got a lot more fun when the Internet came around."},{"time":115000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":117000,"text":"Because, not only could people broadcast their stories throughout the world,"},{"time":120000,"text":"but they could do so"},{"time":122000,"text":"using what seemed to be an infinite amount of devices."},{"time":125000,"text":"For example, one company"},{"time":128000,"text":"would tell a story of love"},{"time":130000,"text":"through its very own search engine."},{"time":135000,"text":"One Taiwanese production studio"},{"time":137000,"text":"would interpret American politics in 3D."},{"time":140000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":145000,"text":"And one man would tell the stories of his father"},{"time":149000,"text":"by using a platform called Twitter"},{"time":151000,"text":"to communicate the excrement his father would gesticulate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":154000,"text":"And after all this, everyone paused;"},{"time":156000,"text":"they took a step back."},{"time":158000,"text":"They realized that, in 6,000 years of storytelling,"},{"time":161000,"text":"they've gone from depicting hunting on cave walls"},{"time":165000,"text":"to depicting Shakespeare on Facebook walls."},{"time":169000,"text":"And this was a cause for celebration."},{"time":172000,"text":"The art of storytelling has remained unchanged."},{"time":174000,"text":"And for the most part, the stories are recycled."},{"time":177000,"text":"But the way that humans tell the stories"},{"time":179000,"text":"has always evolved"},{"time":181000,"text":"with pure, consistent novelty."}]},{"cues":[{"time":184000,"text":"And they remembered a man,"},{"time":186000,"text":"one amazing German,"},{"time":189000,"text":"every time a new storytelling device"},{"time":193000,"text":"popped up next."},{"time":195000,"text":"And for that,"},{"time":197000,"text":"the audience --"},{"time":199000,"text":"the lovely, beautiful audience --"},{"time":201000,"text":"would live happily ever after."},{"time":204000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}